                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/841b: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="20" xml:id="d108fn20">The same telegram was sent to the
                        Embassies in France and Italy.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-03T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 3, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President ratified the London Naval Treaty, 1936, on May 28. So far no other
                    Government has ratified although the Treaty was drafted to come into effect on
                    January 1, 1937. Any information which may come to you with regard to the
                    intentions of the Government to which you are accredited in respect of
                    ratification of the Treaty should be promptly reported.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
